                <h1>Does Shoplifting Appear on Background Checks?</h1>
                <p>Shoplifting can show up on a background check, depending on whether the offense was classified as a misdemeanor or felony and if it resulted in a conviction. Arrest records may also be included in some checks. Employers or organizations may have access to this information, impacting job applications and opportunities.</p>
